    <article class="main-content">

        

        


    



<section class="row c-description" id="section-description">
    <div id="about" class="small-12 columns">
        
        



        
        
            
            <p itemprop="description" class="description">
                ******************************************************************************<br>
<br>
Please note that this project (and all downloads) can be now be found at:<br>
<a href="https://totalnonsense.com/open-source-vector-playing-cards" rel="nofollow noopener">https://totalnonsense.com/open-source-vector-playing-cards</a><br>
<br>
******************************************************************************<br>
<br>
This is a set of poker size playing cards which has been hand crafted in a standard Vector Format (.SVG).   All 52 faces are offered in one file as separate objects that can easily be cut/pasted/exported singly as desired.<br>
<br>
These are licensed under LPGL 3.0.
            </p>
            
    </div>
</section>



        
        
<section class="row psp-section collapsible-section">
    <div class="small-12 columns">
        <h3>Features</h3>
        <ul class="features as-columns"><li class="feature">All 52 modern playing card faces plus 3 Jokers</li><li class="feature">Optimized for size and compatible with modern web Browsers</li><li class="feature">Multiple  different sets offered (Color, Grayscale, B/W, Black/White)</li><li class="feature">Printable versions (Full Bleed) available</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</section>
        
        
